@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{magit-extra.el} extends @samp{magit}, the popular Git interface for Emacs, with convenience commands and workflow automation. The package depends on @samp{magit} and @samp{paths}.

The extensions fall into several categories:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Streamlined commit workflows.} Commands that stage, commit, and push in a single step, reducing the friction of routine Git operations (@ref{Stage commit and push, , Stage@comma{} commit@comma{} and push}).
@item
@strong{Repository maintenance.} Batch updates across multiple repositories and automatic submodule management (@ref{Repository maintenance}).
@item
@strong{Safety guards.} Dirty-repository warnings and confirmation prompts before pushing to production branches (@ref{Dirty repository detection}).
@item
@strong{Asynchronous operations.} Background pulling for repositories that need periodic synchronization (@ref{Asynchronous pull}).
@item
@strong{Customized dispatch menu.} A modified Magit dispatch transient that overrides the default, providing a tailored command palette (@ref{Dispatch menu}).
@item
@strong{Submodule transient suffixes.} Additional entries for the Magit submodule transient menu (@ref{Transient suffixes}).
@end itemize

