@node Asynchronous pull
@section Asynchronous pull

@findex magit-extra-async-pull
The function @code{magit-extra-async-pull} starts a background @samp{git pull} process for REPO without blocking Emacs. It creates an asynchronous process and reports errors via @code{message} if the pull does not finish cleanly. This is useful for keeping repositories synchronized in the background, for instance from a timer or init hook.

@node Automatic submodule pull
@section Automatic submodule pull

@findex magit-extras-pull-including-submodules
The function @code{magit-extras-pull-including-submodules} is installed as @samp{:after} advice on @code{magit-pull}. Whenever you pull in a repository that contains a @samp{.gitmodules} file, this function automatically updates all submodules recursively by calling @code{magit-extras-pull-all-submodules}. This saves you from having to remember to update submodules manually after each pull.

@node Production branch guard
@section Production branch guard

Accidentally pushing to a production branch can have serious consequences. The internal function @code{magit-extras--guard-production} is installed as @samp{:before} advice on both @code{magit-push-current-to-pushremote} and @code{magit-push-current-to-upstream}. When the target branch name contains the string ``production'', the function prompts for confirmation with @code{yes-or-no-p} before allowing the push to proceed. If the user declines, the push is cancelled with a @code{user-error}.

@node Transient suffixes
@chapter Transient suffixes

@findex magit-extras-update-all-submodules
@findex magit-extras-pull-all-submodules
The package defines two transient suffix commands intended for inclusion in Magit's submodule transient menu:

The suffix @code{magit-extras-update-all-submodules} runs @samp{git submodule update --init} with optional @samp{--recursive} arguments. This initializes any uninitialized submodules and checks out the exact commit recorded in the superproject. It does @emph{not} pull the latest changes from the submodule remotes, making it suitable for reproducing a known state.

The suffix @code{magit-extras-pull-all-submodules} runs @samp{git submodule foreach --recursive git pull}, which fetches and merges the latest changes from each submodule's default upstream branch. Unlike @code{magit-extras-update-all-submodules}, this updates submodules to their latest development state regardless of what the superproject records.

Both suffixes accept the standard @code{magit-submodule-arguments} for the @samp{--recursive} flag and run asynchronously.

