@node URL and file helpers
@section URL and file helpers

@findex magit-extras-parse-url
@findex magit-extras-get-commit-file
@findex magit-extras-get-commit-heading
@findex magit-extras-get-unstaged-files
@findex magit-extras-track-file
@findex magit-extras-move-point-to-start
@findex magit-extras-midnight-update
The function @code{magit-extras-parse-url} converts a Git remote URL in SSH format (e.g., @samp{git@@github.com:user/repo.git}) into an HTTPS URL@. It passes HTTP URLs through unchanged.

The function @code{magit-extras-get-commit-file} returns the first staged file in the current repository, querying @samp{git} via @code{magit-staged-files}. It accepts an optional PATH argument: @code{'full} returns the absolute path, @code{'sans-dir} returns only the filename, and @code{nil} (the default) returns the path relative to the repository root.

The function @code{magit-extras-get-commit-heading} retrieves the Org mode heading associated with the code being committed. It parses the diff in the commit buffer to find the first changed line number, visits the file at that line, and returns the enclosing heading via @code{org-entry-get}. This is useful for generating commit messages from Org structure.

The function @code{magit-extras-get-unstaged-files} returns a list of unstaged file names using @samp{git diff --name-only --diff-filter=d}. The function @code{magit-extras-track-file} stages a single file with @samp{git add}. The function @code{magit-extras-move-point-to-start} moves point to the beginning of the buffer after a brief delay, which can be useful in Magit hooks.

The function @code{magit-extras-midnight-update} performs a stage-commit-push
cycle in the given DIRECTORY with the commit message ``Midnight update''.
Before staging, it calls @code{magit-extras-revert-clean-buffers-in-directory}
to refresh stale Emacs buffers, preventing on-disk changes made by
external tools from being overwritten (@ref{Reverting stale buffers}).
It is called by @code{magit-extras-stage-commit-and-push-all-repos}
(@ref{Stage commit and push, , Stage@comma{} commit@comma{} and push}).

@node Reverting stale buffers
@section Reverting stale buffers

@findex magit-extras-revert-clean-buffers-in-directory
The function @code{magit-extras-revert-clean-buffers-in-directory} reverts
all unmodified file-visiting buffers whose files reside under
DIRECTORY@.  A buffer is reverted only when its file still exists on
disk and the buffer has no unsaved edits.  This ensures that external
modifications---from scripts, command-line tools, or other
processes---are picked up by Emacs before a commit.

This function is called automatically by @code{magit-extras-midnight-update}
before staging.  Without it, the @code{files-extras-save-all-buffers} step
(which runs earlier in the @code{midnight-hook}) could overwrite on-disk
changes with stale buffer contents, silently deleting work done
outside Emacs.

